ANACT relativetotheassaultofemergencyroompersonnel.
BeitEnactedbytheSenateandHouseofRepresentativesinGeneralCourtconvened:
1 1 Assault and Related Offenses; First Degree Assault. Amend RSA 631:1, I(c)-(d) to read as
2 follows:
3 (c) Purposelyorknowinglycausesinjurytoanotherresultinginmiscarriageorstillbirth;
4 [or]
5 (d) Knowingly or recklessly causes serious bodily injury to a person under 13 years of
6 age;or
7 (e) Knowingly causes serious bodily injury to any emergency room personnel
8 acting in the line of duty. For purposes of this subparagraph, "emergency room personnel"
9 means a person in a hospital emergency department who, in the course and scope of their
10 employment or as a volunteer, provides services or medical care, or who assists in the
11 providing of services or medical care, for the benefit of the general public, including, but
12 not limited to, any health care professional, emergency department clerk, emergency
13 department technician, student, and emergency department volunteer working in the
14 hospitalemergencydepartment.
15 2 Assault and Related Offenses; Second Degree Assault. Amend RSA 631:2, I(e)-(f) to read as
16 follows:
17 (e) Recklessly or negligently causes injury to another resulting in miscarriage or
18 stillbirth;[or]
19 (f) Purposelyorknowinglyengagesinthestrangulationofanother;or
20 (g) Knowingly causes bodily injury to any emergency room personnel acting in
21 the line of duty. For purposes of this subparagraph, "emergency room personnel" means a
22 person in a hospital emergency department who, in the course and scope of their
23 employment or as a volunteer, provides services or medical care, or who assists in the
24 providing of services or medical care, for the benefit of the general public, including, but
25 not limited to, any health care professional, emergency department clerk, emergency
26 department technician, student, and emergency department volunteer working in the
27 hospitalemergencydepartment.
28 3 EffectiveDate. ThisactshalltakeeffectJanuary1,2027.

